<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,418,715]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,318,534,560]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[325,439,535,560]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Congridae" genus="Ariosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anguilliformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[325,439,535,560]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Ariosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. is being tentatively identified in the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[987,1101,535,560]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Congridae" genus="Ariosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anguilliformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[987,1101,535,560]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Ariosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, despite its lower number of lateral line pores to the level of the anus (e.g. 
<quantity box="[684,743,573,599]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.636" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" unit="in" value="34.0">34 in</quantity>
our specimen 
<emphasis box="[913,945,573,598]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">vs.</emphasis>
<quantity box="[952,1056,573,599]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2446" metricValueMax="1.3208" metricValueMin="1.1684" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" unit="in" value="49.0" valueMax="52.0" valueMin="46.0">46–52 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName box="[1062,1228,573,598]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Congridae" genus="Ariosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anguilliformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="balearicum">
<emphasis box="[1062,1228,573,598]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">A. balearicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); further material is needed for a more precise identification. Leptocephali of 
<taxonomicName box="[853,1019,612,637]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Congridae" genus="Ariosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anguilliformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="balearicum">
<emphasis box="[853,1019,612,637]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">A. balearicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were recorded off 
<collectingCountry box="[1243,1315,612,638]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Brazil</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Castro" pageId="6" pageNumber="19" refString="Castro, M. S. &amp; Bonecker, A. C. T. (2004) Leptocephali collected off the eastern coast of Brazil (12 o - 23 o S). Zootaxa, 935, 1 - 28." type="journal article" year="2004">
Castro and Bonecker (
<number box="[331,396,650,676]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="2004.0">2004</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, and may represent the species reported herein, since adults of that species were never reported from the area.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
